[8]The G.12 inspired the postwar G.212 "Flying Classroom", the last Italian three-engine transporter.
[7]Only a limited number were built, some as late as 1944, after the Italian armistice.
Diagonal:2, Size:3
[6]Access was via a port-side access door aft of the wing.The G.12 was designed as a civil aircraft, but served mainly in military roles during the war.
